</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-40_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NASUWT serves multiple roles, each critical to the educational landscape in the UK. These roles include:
























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-42_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Advocacy and representation</strong> - NASUWT represents the interests of its members by advocating for fair pay, reasonable working hours, and improved working conditions. The union actively negotiates with government bodies to influence educational policy and legislation.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong></strong><strong>Professional development</strong> -&nbsp;The union provides its members a wide range of professional development opportunities. These include workshops, seminars, and training programmes to enhance teachers' skills and knowledge.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-47_ pf-text-1"><strong>Support and guidance </strong>- NASUWT offers support and guidance to teachers on various issues, including legal matters, employment disputes, and workplace challenges. The union's legal team can provide advice and representation when needed.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-49_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and safety </strong>- Ensuring the health and safety of teachers and students is a key priority for NASUWT. The union collaborates with schools and regulatory bodies to develop and implement safety standards and protocols.













</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-51_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-52_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-53_ pf-heading-1-h3">Implementation of relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-55_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NASUWT is crucial in implementing legislation and regulations within the education sector. Key areas of focus include:



























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-57_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-58_ pf-text-1"><strong>Teachers' pay and conditions</strong> - NASUWT has been a leading voice in advocating for fair pay and better working conditions for teachers. This includes ensuring compliance with the School Teachers' Pay and Conditions Document (STPCD) and other relevant regulations.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-60_ pf-text-1"><strong>Workplace safety</strong> - Collaborating with the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) and other regulatory bodies, NASUWT helps schools implement effective health and safety policies, which ensures a safe working environment for teachers and students alike.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-62_ pf-text-1"><strong>Equality and diversity</strong> - NASUWT champions equality and diversity within schools. The union promotes compliance with the Equality Act 2010, which aims to eliminate discrimination and promote equality of opportunity.













