</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-70_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-71_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage with unions </strong>- Schools should actively engage with unions like NASUWT to understand the needs and concerns of their staff. This helps in creating a supportive and collaborative working environment.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-73_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training </strong>- Continuous professional development is essential for teachers. Schools should provide regular training sessions on relevant legislation, health and safety protocols, and equality and diversity practices.

